<h2>Discover Dalhousie Real Estate</h2>
<p>The community in Dalhousie established itself in the year 1967 and named the location after George Ramsay, the 9th Earl of the community Dalhousie.</p>
<p>Dalhousie homes for sale include an eclectic mix of housing options ranging from single family homes, to bungalows, apartments and condo units, some of which were constructed back in the 70s. The average price of residential properties in Dalhousie is over $ 400,000 with the price climbing higher to $1.5 million for the more premium units.</p>
<p>Dalhousie homes for sale have been on the rise due to the fact that this neighborhood enjoys a host of green spaces. Additionally, the Crowchild Trail to the south serves as a convenient escape route to the Rockies, which is a pleasant piece of news to those who like heading out during the weekends.</p>
<p>Also, The Dalhousie Community Association offers a wide variety of recreational programs for its residents such as sports, golf courses, playgroups, Boy scouts, health clubs and so on.</p>
</div>
